docs/command-reference.md:204:- The EMSD package now also exists in code, not just in notes: `my-claw/curriculum/` contains a full course catalog and scaffold generator, and the new production-side helpers are `sound_palette_lab.py`, `sample_lab.py`, `mix_engine.py`, `procedural_arc.py`, `dsp_scene_lab.py`, `artistic_identity.py`, and `capstone_engine.py`.
docs/command-reference.md:223:- `restart_composer.sh` now also performs a second non-destructive `sw_master_smooth` seed after the new composer PID is confirmed alive. That compensates for the composer's startup `/g_freeAll`, which would otherwise leave early scene-level master-bus `/n_set` traffic writing to a dead node.
docs/command-reference.md:227:- `restart_composer.sh` now waits for a healthy steady-state `duet_composer.py` process instead of only validating the first short-lived child PID returned by `nohup`, which avoids false failure reports during the current live startup race. It also launches the composer with `nohup setsid ... </dev/null` so operator SSH teardown does not kill the live music process.
