./sdp/verification/t-024@20260416t054258z-verify.md:22:All 11 required topic areas are covered with at least one exercise each. EMSD-302 provides both `ex01` (progressions) and `ex02` (counterpoint), satisfying two topic requirements from a single course as specified. The `_ex()` helper correctly defaults template to `{feature: True}` when no explicit template is provided, ensuring all verifier stubs can run even for minimal exercises. 16 committed `spec.json` files match the 16 courses with exercises in the catalog.
./sdp/verification/t-024@20260416t054258z-verify.md:26:Exercise specs follow the established `_ex()` factory pattern consistently. Verifier kinds are restricted to the four declared variants (`structural`, `constraint`, `spectral`, `temporal`). The catalog-level structure and generated file structure are kept in sync via `materialize_curriculum()`. The `expected` property correctly aliases `expected_features` for backward compatibility. Exercise IDs (`ex01`, `ex02`) are unique within each course.
